            costInfo: "Research Chemical Vendors: ~$25-$45 per 2mg vial.",
            deepDive: "CJC-1295 is a tetrasubstituted 30-amino acid peptide hormone, primarily functioning as a GHRH analog.\n\nMod GRF 1-29 (No DAC): The first 29 amino acids of GHRH were modified with four amino acid substitutions (D-Ala2, Gln8, Ala15, Leu27) to prevent rapid degradation by DPP-4 enzymes, extending the half-life from Sermorelin's 10 minutes to approximately 30 minutes.\n\nCJC-1295 (With DAC): A Drug Affinity Complex (DAC) containing a maleimidopropionic acid linker is added to the C-terminus. This allows the peptide to covalently bind to endogenous serum albumin after injection, protecting it from clearance and extending the half-life to 6-8 days.\n\nMechanism Deep Dive:\nLike Sermorelin, CJC-1295 binds to the GHRH receptor on pituitary somatotrophs, activating the cAMP/PKA pathway to stimulate GH transcription and release. However, the 'With DAC' version's continuous presence means the receptor is constantly stimulated. This leads to a continuous elevation of basal GH and IGF-1 levels (a 'GH bleed') rather than discrete physiological pulses. Over time, this continuous stimulation can lead to receptor downregulation (desensitization) and impaired glucose tolerance.\n\nClinical Trial Summary:\nCJC-1295 (With DAC) underwent Phase 2 clinical trials by ConjuChem. A single injection increased mean plasma GH concentrations by 2- to 10-fold for 6 days or more, and IGF-1 levels by 1.5- to 3-fold for 9-11 days. The trials were halted after a patient died of a myocardial infarction. While the death was ultimately deemed unrelated to the drug (the patient had severe pre-existing cardiovascular disease), development was abandoned.\n\nSynergy with GHRPs: The combination of CJC-1295 and a GHRP (like Ipamorelin or GHRP-6) is profoundly synergistic. GHRH analogs increase the number of somatotrophs releasing GH, while GHRPs increase the amount of GH released per cell and simultaneously inhibit somatostatin.\n\nThe 'DAC' Debate: The community consensus is overwhelmingly against using CJC-1295 With DAC. The continuous GH bleed is unnatural, causes massive water retention, and ruins insulin sensitivity. 'No DAC' (Mod GRF 1-29) is the gold standard.\n\nLong-Term Use Data: Long-term use of CJC-1295 With DAC is strongly discouraged due to the risk of insulin resistance and receptor downregulation. The No DAC version is considered safe for 12-16 week cycles.",
