                FAQItem(question: "Will it help me lose subcutaneous fat (the fat I can pinch)?", answer: "Yes, elevated growth hormone will aid in total body fat loss. However, clinical trials showed its most profound and statistically significant effect is on visceral fat (the hard fat under the muscle wall)."),
                FAQItem(question: "Do I have to inject it with Ipamorelin?", answer: "No. Because the dose of Tesamorelin is so high (1-2mg), it is highly effective on its own. However, stacking it with a low dose of Ipamorelin (100-200mcg) will maximize the GH pulse."),
                FAQItem(question: "Why do my hands hurt/tingle when I wake up?", answer: "This is carpal tunnel syndrome caused by water retention compressing the median nerve in your wrist. It is a hallmark sign of high GH levels. If it becomes painful, lower your dose to 1mg."),
                FAQItem(question: "Is it safe if I don't have HIV?", answer: "Yes. While it was approved specifically for HIV-associated lipodystrophy (because insurance companies needed a specific disease state to bill against), the mechanism of action (releasing your own natural growth hormone) works exactly the same in healthy individuals."),
