                FAQItem(question: "Why do I have to wait to eat after injecting if it makes me so hungry?", answer: "When you eat carbohydrates or fats, your body releases insulin and free fatty acids. These trigger the release of somatostatin, a hormone that acts like a 'stop' signal to your pituitary gland. If you eat immediately, you will blunt the GH release. You must suffer through the hunger for 30-45 minutes to get the GH benefit before eating."),
